        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2–2449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-24">February 24,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received February 24—5:40 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>456. Nanking vernacular February 22 reports important meeting to be held this
                    week presided by Li Tsung-jen, who has invited Chang Chun,<note n="69" xml:id="d176fn69">Administrator of Political and Military Affairs for
                        Southwest China.</note> Hunan Governor Cheng Chien, Chang Chih-chung, Pai
                    Chung-hsi, Chung Tien-hsin and Peng Chao-hsien. Last three reported already in
                    Nanking while February 23 press prominently reports Chang Chih-chung arrival
                    Nanking.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated AmEmb Canton 98, Shanghai 212.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
